dc_title_s: [Geological Survey of England and Wales : one inch to the mile map. New Series.] Liverpool, solid, sheet 96
dc_description_s: Geological Survey of Great Britain. Great Britain. Geological Survey of England and Wales. Sheet 96 solid. Great Britain. Ordnance Survey of England. North Decimal Degree 53.433300. South Decimal Degree 53.2667. East Decimal Degree -2.9167. West Decimal Degree -3.3500. In upper left margin: Ordnance Survey of England and Wales. Relief shown by contour interval and spot heights.Transverse Mercator projection. National grid system. Depth shown by form lines and contour intervals. "Original Geological Survey on the one-inch scale published on Quarter Sheets 79 N.E. & S.E. (Old Series), in 1850, Revised 1884 & 1886 on the six-inch scale by C. E. De Rance et al. Coal Measures & Trias re-surveyeyd by C. B. Wedd et al. from 1911-1920.".
dc_publisher_s: [Southampton ; Chessington, Surrey] : Director General, Ordnance Survey, 1923.
